BOLD FACE denotes Committee Amendments.

1 1. Two rearview mirrors, containing a reflection surface of not
2 less than three (3) inches in diameter, mounted one on each side of
3 the motorcycle and positioned so as to enable the operator to
4 clearly view the roadway to the rear of the vehicle;
5 2. A windshield of sufficient quality, size and thickness to
6 protect the operator from foreign objects, except that in lieu of
7 such windshield, the operator shall wear goggles or other protective
8 eyewear which meets American National Standards Institute (ANSI)
9 Standard Z87.1 and provides positive retention, or a face shield of
10 material and design to protect the operator from foreign objects;
11 3. A properly operating speedometer capable of registering at
12 least the maximum legal speed limit for that motorcycle;
13 4. A fender over each wheel. All fenders shall be of the type
14 provided by the manufacturer;
15 5. A horn which shall comply with the requirements of Section
16 12-401 of this title; and
17 6. A muffler or other effective noise-suppressing system which
18 shall comply with the requirements of Section 12-402 of this title.
19 B. No person under eighteen (18) years of age shall operate or
20 ride upon any motorcycle unless such person is properly wearing a
21 crash helmet of a type which complies with standards established by
22 49 C.F.R., Section 571.218.
23 C. Handlebars on motorcycles shall not be higher than eye level
24 of the operator.
